<h1>Openfore Community Guidelines</h1>

<p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> March 7, 2026</p>

<div class="company-box">

<p><strong>Platform:</strong> Openfore</p>
<p><strong>Operated by:</strong> PickyClicky Inc.</p>
<p><strong>Address:</strong> 1653 Woodbine Heights Blvd., East York, Ontario, M4B 3A7, Canada</p>

</div>

<p>
Openfore is designed to connect golfers with other golfers and create opportunities
to enjoy the game together. These Community Guidelines help ensure that the platform
remains safe, respectful, and enjoyable for everyone.
</p>

<p>
By using Openfore, you agree to follow these guidelines in addition to the
Openfore Terms of Service.
</p>

<h2>1. Respect Other Members</h2>

<p>
Treat other golfers with courtesy and respect both online and in person.
</p>

<p>The following behavior is not allowed:</p>

<ul>

<li>Harassment, threats, or intimidation</li>

<li>Hate speech or discrimination based on race, religion, gender, nationality, sexual orientation, disability, or other protected characteristics</li>

<li>Personal attacks or abusive language</li>

<li>Unwanted repeated messages or harassment</li>

</ul>

<h2>2. Be Honest and Authentic</h2>

<p>
Users must provide truthful information when participating in the platform.
</p>

<p>Prohibited actions include:</p>

<ul>

<li>Creating fake profiles</li>

<li>Impersonating another person</li>

<li>Misrepresenting golf bookings or tee times</li>

<li>Using misleading or deceptive information</li>

</ul>

<h2>3. No Spam or Unauthorized Promotion</h2>

<p>
Openfore is intended for golfers connecting with other golfers.
</p>

<p>The following activities are prohibited:</p>

<ul>

<li>Spam messages or mass invitations</li>

<li>Unauthorized advertising or marketing</li>

<li>Posting commercial offers unrelated to golf participation</li>

<li>Soliciting personal information for unrelated purposes</li>

</ul>

<h2>4. Protect User Safety</h2>

<p>
Users should exercise good judgment when interacting with others.
</p>

<p>
Openfore does not supervise or verify users and cannot guarantee the behavior
of individuals you may meet through the platform.
</p>

<p>For your safety:</p>

<ul>

<li>Meet in public locations such as golf courses</li>

<li>Confirm tee times directly with the course</li>

<li>Avoid sharing sensitive personal information</li>

<li>Report suspicious behavior</li>

</ul>

<h2>5. No Illegal Activity</h2>

<p>
Users must not use the Service for unlawful activities including:
</p>

<ul>

<li>Fraud or scams</li>

<li>Financial exploitation</li>

<li>Threats or violence</li>

<li>Posting illegal materials</li>

</ul>

<h2>6. Respect Golf Courses and Facilities</h2>

<p>
When coordinating rounds through Openfore, users must respect the rules
and policies of golf courses.
</p>

<p>This includes:</p>

<ul>

<li>Following course etiquette</li>

<li>Respecting pace of play</li>

<li>Complying with course rules</li>

<li>Treating staff and players respectfully</li>

</ul>

<h2>7. Respect Privacy</h2>

<p>
Do not post or share another user's personal information without permission.
</p>

<p>
Private conversations should not be publicly disclosed without consent.
</p>

<h2>8. Prohibited Technical Behavior</h2>

<p>
Users must not attempt to interfere with the operation of the platform.
</p>

<p>This includes:</p>

<ul>

<li>Using bots or automated tools</li>

<li>Scraping user data</li>

<li>Reverse engineering the platform</li>

<li>Attempting to bypass security features</li>

</ul>

<h2>9. Reporting Violations</h2>

<p>
If you encounter behavior that violates these guidelines, please report it.
</p>

<p>Reports can be submitted to:</p>

<p><strong>legal@pickyclicky.com</strong></p>

<h2>10. Enforcement</h2>

<p>
Openfore may take action against users who violate these guidelines.
</p>

<p>Possible actions include:</p>

<ul>

<li>Content removal</li>

<li>Account warnings</li>

<li>Temporary suspension</li>

<li>Permanent account termination</li>

</ul>

<p>
Openfore reserves the right to determine violations at its sole discretion.
</p>

<h2>11. Changes to the Guidelines</h2>

<p>
These guidelines may be updated periodically to reflect platform
changes or community needs.
</p>

<p>
Continued use of Openfore indicates acceptance of updated guidelines.
</p>

